@startuml
title Email Change via OTP Verification

actor "Client Manager" as client
participant "<<interface>>\nSettings\nScreen" as settings #A9C4E9
participant "<<control>>\nAuth Service\n(Supabase)" as auth #FDB983
participant "<<service>>\nSMTP\nMail Server" as smtp #C5E0B4
participant "<<interface>>\nOTP Verification\nScreen" as otp #A9C4E9
participant "<<entity>>\nauth.users\n(PostgreSQL)" as db #FFE599

== Step 1: Initiate Email Change ==
client -> settings: 1 Input new email address
settings -> auth: 2 updateUser(email: newEmail)
auth -> smtp: 3 Dispatch Email Change OTP to current email
smtp --> client: 4 Deliver OTP code to current mailbox
auth --> settings: 5 Return OTP status (needs confirmation)
settings --> client: 6 Render OTP input screen

== Step 2: OTP Verification ==
client -> otp: 7 Enter OTP code from email
alt incorrect or expired
    otp -> auth: 8 verifyOTP(email, token, type: emailChange)
    auth --> otp: 9 Error — invalid or expired OTP
    otp --> client: 10 Display error, allow retry
else valid
    otp -> auth: 11 verifyOTP(email, token, type: emailChange)
    auth -> smtp: 12 Dispatch Email Change Confirm to new email
    smtp --> client: 13 Deliver confirmation email to new mailbox
    auth -> db: 14 UPDATE auth.users SET email = newEmail
    db --> auth: 15 Email updated successfully
    auth --> otp: 16 Email change complete
    otp --> client: 17 Show success toast notification
end

@enduml